        <name>1.2.4.3 Write fractions and decimals</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Write the following numbers using a positive index and also express your answers as decimal fractions: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a fraction, \({@a1@}= \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a decimal, \({@a1@}= \)[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a fraction, \({@b1@}= \)  [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a decimal, \({@b1@}= \) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a fraction, \({@c1@}= \)  [[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]] [[feedback:prt5]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a decimal, \({@c1@}= \)  [[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]] [[feedback:prt6]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Using the fact that \( a^{-m} = \dfrac{1}{a^m} \) we can see \({@a1@} = \displaystyle {@ta1@}. \)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Now, converting the answer from a fraction to a decimal we obtain \(\displaystyle{@ta1@} = {@ta2@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt; 

    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Using the fact that \( a^{-m} = \dfrac{1}{a^m} \) we can see \({@b1@} = \displaystyle{@ta3@} .\)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Now, converting the answer from a fraction to a decimal we obtain \(\displaystyle{@ta3@} = {@ta4@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;

    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Using the fact that \( a^{-m} = \dfrac{1}{a^m} \) we can see \({@c1@} = \displaystyle{@ta5@} .\)&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Now, converting the answer from a fraction to a decimal we obtain \(\displaystyle{@ta5@} = {@ta6@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
